# Tab Control - KX Dashboards

Original URL: https://code.kx.com/dashboards/tabcontrol/

# Tab Control

![Screenshot](../img/tabcontrol/tabmenuexamplehtmllight.jpg)  
_A Tab Control with five tabs. The first Tab, Trade Performance, is selected
and visible_

A container of displays selected by a tab menu. A tab can hold a single
component or a [Layout panel](../layout/) with multiple components.

## Set up

  1. Define the number of tabs you require.

  2. Within each tab element, add a single component, [layout panel](../layout/), or [flex panel](../flexpanel/) for multiple components. 

## _Basics_

![Screenshot](../img/tabcontrol/tabcontrolbasics.png)

_Name_

    A name for the component provided by the user. 

## View State

![Screenshot](../img/tabcontrol/tabsmenu2.jpg)

_Selected Tab_

    

The Tab visible at launch

Linking Tab Controls

To link Tabs in two separate Tab Controls (so that clicking on Tab 1 of Tab
Control 1 opens Tab 1 of Tab Control 2), create a [View State
Parameter](../viewstateparameters/) and assign it to _Selected Tab_ of Tab
Control 1 and Tab Control 2.

![Screenshot](../img/tabcontrol/linkedtab.jpg)

_Unload Inactive Tabs_

    When enabled, uploaded tab content will be removed on tab switch.
_Set View State on Tab Change_

    

In addition to linking different tab components, switching tabs can be used to
assign a value to a View State Parameter; for example, if looking to reset a
default value on tab switch.

![Screenshot](../img/tabcontrol/setviestateontabchangehtmllight.jpg)

## Tabs

![Screenshot](../img/tabcontrol/tabsmenu.jpg)

A Tab can be hidden by checking its _Hide_ box. Hiding a Tab does not remove
it, just the means to click its tab. Navigation to the hidden tab content can
be achieved using a [Button](../button/).

_Name_

    Name displayed in tab
_Tooltip_

    Description of tab on mouse rollover
_Hide_

    Hide display of tab

## Style

[Style](../style/#component-style) for common settings

